        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Are free APIs reliable for production use? <span class="faq-icon">&#9660;</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Many free APIs are reliable for side projects and MVPs, but for mission-critical production use, you should evaluate their uptime guarantees, rate limits, and SLA. Often, transitioning to a paid tier is necessary as your application scales.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">How do I handle API rate limits on free tiers? <span class="faq-icon">&#9660;</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>To handle rate limits, implement caching to reduce redundant requests, use queues to pace your outbound calls, and implement exponential backoff strategies for retrying failed requests when limits are hit.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Do free APIs require authentication? <span class="faq-icon">&#9660;</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Most high-quality free APIs require authentication via an API key or OAuth. This allows providers to track usage, enforce rate limits, and prevent abuse, even on their free tiers.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">What is the difference between REST and GraphQL APIs? <span class="faq-icon">&#9660;</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>REST APIs expose multiple endpoints for different resources and use standard HTTP methods, while GraphQL exposes a single endpoint and allows clients to request exactly the data they need, reducing over-fetching.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I monetize an app built entirely on free APIs? <span class="faq-icon">&#9660;</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes, you can monetize apps built with free APIs, but you must carefully read the Terms of Service for each API. Some providers explicitly forbid commercial use of their free tiers or require attribution.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Which free APIs work without an API key? <span class="faq-icon">&#9660;</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Several popular APIs require no authentication: Open-Meteo (weather), REST Countries, JSONPlaceholder, PokeAPI, Dictionary API, RandomUser.me, NASA APOD, Lorem Picsum, The Cat API, The Dog API, and QR Server. These are ideal for learning and prototyping.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
